{"key":"post-8806143","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8806143</id>\n<content>I'd suggest 1 1/2&quot; PVC and the fittings necessary to frame it any size you want.&amp;nbsp; Cover with plastic and you're done.&amp;nbsp; I'd buy any shelving you're going to use so you can base the size frame you build on that.&amp;nbsp; It helps to have the shelves pushed to one side, so you can have a coolmist humidifier down low, giving it an unrestricted path to blow humid air straight up.&amp;nbsp; If your humidifier blows into shelves, the moisture will just condense and drip back down.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8806846</next>\n<prev>8806124</prev>\n<first>8805710</first>\n<last>8806846</last>\n<when>1219351181</when>\n<utime>08/21/08 11:39 PM</utime>\n</post>"}